Title: AtCoder Beginner Contest 391
Name: Seek Grid
Problem Statement:
You are given an N \times N grid S and an M \times M grid T. The cell at the i-th row from the top and the j-th column from the left is denoted by (i,j).
The colors of the cells in S and T are represented by N^2 characters S_{i,j} (1≤ i,j≤ N) and M^2 characters T_{i,j} (1≤ i,j≤ M), respectively. In grid S, cell (i,j) is white if S_{i,j} is ., and black if S_{i,j} is #. The same applies for grid T.
Find T within S. More precisely, output integers a and b (1 ≤ a,b ≤ N-M+1) that satisfy the following condition:
- S_{a+i-1,b+j-1} = T_{i,j} for every i,j (1≤ i,j ≤ M).
Constraints:
- 1 ≤ M ≤ N ≤ 50
- N and M are integers.
- Each of S_{i,j} and T_{i,j} is . or #.
- There is exactly one pair (a,b) satisfying the condition.

Sample Detail.explanation: The 2 \times 2 subgrid of S from the 2nd to the 3rd row and from the 2nd to the 3rd column matches T.
